  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-chicken-and-brown-rice-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place your hand flat onto the<strong> chicken breast fillet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-chicken-and-brown-rice-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), with a matching lid, over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p>\r\n<p>Add a couple of splashes of <strong>water</strong> to the pan and cover with a lid</p>\r\n<p>Cook for a further 10-15 min or until the <strong>chicken</strong> is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-chicken-and-brown-rice-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>red</strong>&nbsp;<strong>chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop ﬁnely</p>\r\n<p>Roll the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice!) and cut in half</p>\r\n<p>Combine the<strong> rice vinegar</strong>,<strong> lime juice</strong>,<strong> chopped chilli</strong>&nbsp;and<strong>&nbsp;fish sauce</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>in a small bowl &ndash; this is your <strong>Vietnamese dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-chicken-and-brown-rice-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the<strong> carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\">,</span> then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot 'ribbons'</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>cucumber<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half, scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon and slice finely</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>radishes</strong> as finely as you can into thin rounds</p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>carrot ribbons</strong>,<strong> sliced cucumber</strong> and<strong> radishes </strong>with the<strong> Vietnamese dressing </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt&nbsp;</strong>in a large bowl&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-chicken-and-brown-rice-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Trim and finely slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the<strong> roasted peanuts</strong> coarsely (or bash them in their bag)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-chicken-and-brown-rice-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the&nbsp;<strong>chicken</strong>&nbsp;is cooked, transfer it to a plate and leave the pan over a medium heat (no need to give it a clean!)</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>soy sauce sachets&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>honey&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 2-3 min, stirring all the time, until the sauce has thickened and is sticky</p>\r\n<p>Once sticky, remove the pan from the heat, return the <strong>chicken</strong> to the pan and turn it in the glaze until it's fully coated</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-chicken-and-brown-rice-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>chicken</strong> and serve over the <strong>brown rice</strong> with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p>\r\n<p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped mint</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>coriander</strong>, <strong>spring onion</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>crushed peanuts&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Drizzle over the<strong> remaining&nbsp;dressing</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
